sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2069006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: pT7 + RBS + Reflectin (+LipA tag) + RBS + Cpn10 + RBS + Cpn60 + RBS + CspC + RBS + Antifungal GAFP-1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: assembly of parts in the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is team Tec-Chihuahua gene expression generator. It expresses the chaperonins of the Cpn10/Cpn60 system for expression of proteins in atypical temperatures as well as the CspC protein, all with a strong RBS and pT7 promoter for high expression. It also expresses the GAFP-1 from Gastrodia and contains a t1 terminator as well as the early T7 phage terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: no special issues in the design
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Mara Valverde Rasc??n

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: assembly of parts from the 2016 distribution kit
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part allows the expression of Reflectin and Cpn10 with the addition of a terminator. It caontains the part BBa_K538100 from Amsterdam's 2011 project icE. coli

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: no special issues in the design

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GAFP-1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This gene was ordered from a synthesis company.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The Gastrodia anti-fungal protein (GAFP-1) is a mannose-binding lectin which is able to inhibit the growth of multiples species of plant pathogenic fungi.
The RBS used is a strong RBS for Bacillus subtilis (K780002).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is composed of a Strong RBS (K780002) and the open reading frame of the Gastrodia anti-fungal protein 1 (GAFP-1) optimized for its expression and its secretion in Bacillus subtilis. The codon optimization was made thanks to the DNA 2.0 software program.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Manon Molina

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K541506
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Reflectin is a self-assembling protein that has the ability to reflect the sun light which depends on the thickness of the protein layer. Therefore, we thought that this ability could be used as a novel reporter for B.subtilis and E.coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Optimized for both B.subtilis and E.coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Fazilet Guler

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Cpn10
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This part encodes the protein ''cochaperonin 10'', which is part of the Cpn10/Cpn60 chaperonin system of ''Oleispira antarctica''.
[More information will follow soon.]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The protein's sequence[1] was published by Ferrer ''et al.'' in 2004. Pre- and suffixes were added to this as clarified in OpenWetWare's BioBrick standards[2] and, as is recommended, the TAA stop codon was replaced with TAATAA. The sequence's conformity with Assembly standard 10[3] was confirmed using the EMBOSS recoder[4], by recoding restriction sites of EcoRI, XbaI, SpeI, PstI, NotI, PvuII, XhoI, AvrII, NheI and SapI.
1 - http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/22266159?from=458&to=751&report=gbwithparts 2 - http://openwetware.org/wiki/Biobrick_standard 3 - http://partsregistry.org/Help:Assembly_standard_10 4 - http://bioweb2.pasteur.fr/docs/EMBOSS/recoder.html
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bas Stringer (Sequence by Paul van Dieken)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
